ure information, teleporting you to the unoccupied space nearest to the spectral mind or to an item bearing one of your artificer infusions, where you physically reappear. You can teleport in this way once for free and must finish a long rest before doing so again. You can also use this special ability by expending a spell slot of 2nd level or higher.","level":14}],"id":"Custom5e94a2c9-bc4b-4e4c-82e1-ebccc77d59c0","isFeature":true,"jsonType":"feat","level":1,"name":"Pure Information ","notes":"","type":"Feat"},"level":14}],"hpModifier":"CON","id":"artificer__revised__archivist_","jsonType":"class","languages":[],"modelType":"Archetype","multiclassArmor":true,"multiclassSkills":true,"multiclassTools":true,"multiclassWeapons":true,"name":"Archivist ","selectableFeatures":[],"shouldShowCompanion":false,"skillProficiencies":[],"specialAbilities":[],"spellSlots":[],"spellcastingAbility":"INT","spells":[{"level":3,"spellModel":{"castingTime":"1 action","classes":"bard, sorcerer, warlock, blood_hunter, wizard","components":"V, S, M (a pinch of soot and salt)","description":"For the duration, you understand the literal meaning of any spoken language that you hear. You also understand any written language that you see, but you must be touching the surface on which the words are written. It takes about 1 minute to read one page of text.\n\nThis spell doesnâ€™t decode secret messages in a text or a glyph, such as an arcane sigil, that isnâ€™t part of a written language.","duration":"1 hour","higherLevels":"","isCustom":false,"isRitual":true,"jsonType":"spell","level":1,"name":"Comprehend Languages","notes":"","pinned":false,"prepared":false,"range":"Self","school":"divination","type":"1st-level divination (Ritual)"}},{"level":3,"spellModel":{"castingTime":"1 action","classes":"bard","components":"V","description":"You whisper a discordant melody that only one creature of your choice within range can hear, wracking it with terrible pain. The target must make a Wisdom saving thr